The '''yellow-billed malkoha''' ('''''Rhamphococcyx calyorhynchus''''') is a species of [[cuckoo]] in the family [[Cuculidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Sulawesi]], [[Indonesia]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s.

It often follows [[moor macaque]]s.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=White |first=Clayton M. |date=October 2010 |title=Birds of Eastern North America: A Photographic Guide and Birds of Western North America: A Photographic Guide'''Birds of Eastern North America: A Photographic Guide.'''2009. Paul Sterry and Brian E. Small . Princeton University Press, Princeton, New Jersey. $18.95, paper, ISBN 978-0-691-13426-0; $45.00, cloth, ISBN 978-0-691-13425-3. 336 pages, 1118 color photographs, 405 maps.'''Birds of Western North America: A Photographic Guide.'''2009. Paul Sterry and Brian E. Small . Princeton University Press, Princeton, New Jersey. $18.95, paper, ISBN 978-0-691-13428-4; $45.00, cloth, ISBN 978-0-691-13427-7. 416 pages, 1314 color photographs, 443 maps. |journal=Western North American Naturalist |volume=70 |issue=3 |pages=421–422 |doi=10.3398/064.070.0317 |issn=1527-0904}}</ref>

